\PYG{g+gs}{**Summary of the Introduction**}

The document begins by describing the current landscape of large language models (LLMs) and the practical issues that arise when using them. It explains that every user input is tokenized, and the model generates predictions based on these tokens. When the total number of tokens exceeds a model’s context window, the system must create summaries and use a condensed context, which helps maintain answer quality while reducing hallucinations. A broader context generally improves an LLM’s ability to analyze large data sets, although larger models require more computational resources.

The introduction then provides a taxonomy of LLM families:

| LLM Family | Key Characteristics |
|\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}|\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}|
| \PYG{g+gs}{**Vision models**} | Include image‑recognition capabilities; can handle prompts like “What is shown in this photo?” together with an image. |
| \PYG{g+gs}{**Multimodal models**} | Can ingest combinations of text, images, video, or audio simultaneously. |
| \PYG{g+gs}{**Mixture‑of‑Experts (MoE)**} | Example: Mixtral 8x7B, which combines multiple specialist sub‑models to deliver strong performance on tasks such as mathematics, multilingual reasoning, and code generation, often outperforming larger models despite having fewer parameters. |

The text notes that “LLM” and “AI” are used interchangeably, as discussions about either effectively refer to deploying a large language model with artificial‑intelligence functionality.

Finally, the introduction outlines the structure of the rest of the document, mentioning forthcoming sections on benchmarking, human‑in‑the‑loop methods, self‑consistency, a proof‑of‑concept applying Retrieval‑Augmented Generation (RAG) to OAS queries, API documentation generation, and Postman test creation. Later chapters will explore the broader impact of AI on users, the environment, the job market, and speculative future developments.

